    {
      "id": "note_spawnable_vs_inventory_item",
      "title": "SpawnableId vs FInventoryItem",
      "cardType": "note",
      "domainId": "ardaria-data-model",
      "x": 217,
      "y": 2574,
      "w": 430,
      "comment": {
        "what": "## SpawnableId vs FInventoryItem\n\n`SpawnableId` is the unique reference to an item type/template.\n\nIt answers: what kind of thing is this? Stone, pickaxe, ore, food, station build piece, etc. This is the stable type identity used to resolve templates, meshes, behavior, and spawn configuration.\n\n`FInventoryItem` is the exact mutable state of one item occurrence.\n\nIt answers: what is the state of this specific item right now? `ItemId`, `SpawnableId`, quantity, power, damage, temperature, composition, buffs, assembled transforms, and other per-occurrence state.\n\n`ItemId` identifies one concrete occurrence. `FInventoryItem.SpawnableId` points back to the type/template.\n\nWorld representation paths:\n\n- `APhysicalItemActor` is a loose world actor carrying the full `FInventoryItem Item`.\n- `UPhysicalStaticMeshComponent` is a lightweight resource particle. It stores `SpawnableId` and creates a new `FInventoryItem` when collected.\n- `UOptimizedInstancedStaticMeshComponent` is the batched/static world representation for placed or generated instances.\n\nPlaced/static item distinction:\n\n- `FBuildComponentSer` is the persistent build/world element projection: type, placement, transform, and build identity.\n- A `UBuildComponent` can represent a placed item or structure. When it represents an item occurrence, its runtime item state lives in `InventoryItemInternal`.\n- Picking up a placed/static item can collapse the optimized instance/build representation and create an `APhysicalItemActor` carrying the item occurrence.\n\nPersistence boundary:\n\n- The build table persists the placed/static projection, not the whole runtime `UBuildComponent`.\n- Loose physical actors and static mesh resource particles are runtime representations until collected, converted, or persisted through another owner.\n- A station can spawn inventory item occurrences, but the spawned occurrence must still be tracked as either an inventory item, a physical actor, or a placed/build representation depending on where it lives.\n\nCritical rule: `SpawnableId` answers type/template identity. `FInventoryItem` answers mutable occurrence state."
      },
      "facts": [],
      "fields": []
    },
    {
      "id": "runtime_physical_item_actor",
      "title": "APhysicalItemActor",
      "cardType": "world-representation",
      "domainId": "ardaria-data-model",
      "x": 268,
      "y": 2292,
      "w": 390,
      "comment": {
        "what": "Loose physical item actor. Carries a full FInventoryItem occurrence and supports physics, magnet collection, pickup, liquids, assemblies, and equipment preview."
      },
