    {
      "id": "card-dd0282d5-7521-4548-a7ad-965fb97d4e89",
      "title": "Quest System",
      "cardType": "note",
      "domainId": "ardaria-data-model",
      "x": 3358,
      "y": 1212,
      "w": 260,
      "comment": {
        "what": "Quest/event evaluation runtime.\n\nAfter each meaningful game event, the game emits a compact event payload for the quest system to evaluate in the background. The event should describe the action with generic tags and ids, for example dialog line activated, item bought, character killed, build placed, item delivered, or station interaction completed.\n\nThe quest system checks active quest states for the character and decides whether any current step predicate is satisfied. This lookup must not block the main interaction flow. The result can advance a quest step, complete a quest, grant rewards, unlock dependent dialog, or trigger UI/highlight feedback.\n\nThis card is the runtime mechanism, separate from `FQuest` authored data, `FQuestStep` authored predicates, and `FQuestState` persisted progress."
      }
    },
